MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: cd20df6c9479f3d449851f4ca53de79e, type: 3}
  m_Name: PlantsBook
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Plants
  spreads:
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: cc6383de98fd6294388821de6cde789f, type: 3}
    textA: 'Some of the local plants have changed recently. I have tried to record
      their changes in this journal. These are not plants. They imitate structure,
      but not purpose.


      Roots without soil.

      Growth without light....'
    textB: They react....not to water, not to time. To us....
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 0}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 4370654923283873279, guid: 10fb891da31975b4e95408080b14b9b9, type: 3}
    textA: 'Some specimens recoil from sudden illumination. Not sustained light,
      but interuption.


      This explains why they are able to survive in the
      daylight.'
    textB: 'A steady beam did nothing. But brief flashes....force it to contract?

      Like
      blinking at something that shouldn''t be there.'
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 0}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 8350bb0e530f4f847bc89e5a6414e355, type: 3}
    textA: 'There seems to be pale variants that do not photosynthesize. They avoid
      natural light entirely!


      They seem to prefer something else...perhaps
      the spiral patterns they have will explain?'
    textB: 'Under the inspection light, they collapse rapidly. Not a burn, but erased..

      As
      if it exposed it for what they really are. Perhaps the UV is responsible for
      why they avoid the daylight?'
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 0}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: cc6383de98fd6294388821de6cde789f, type: 3}
    textA: 'Do not assume they behave like plants! Watering them made them worse.


      Fire
      was....inconclusive.

      Sometimes effective.

      Sometimes it spread.'
    textB: Havn't tried overwatering. Must try as soon as I can!
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: -7845495922271660370, guid: e6ebebfbd034ea848b7eecb414a2f126, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 3671605574920047432, guid: 714783606f1130d46add62045a7e6fbd, type: 3}
    textA: Cutting the surface does nothing. It grows back faster than it is removed.
      But the structure is not uniform. There are points where everything connects.
      If I break those, the whole thing falls. It seems to only work on the ones
      with stripes?
    textB: 
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: -131896887491537849, guid: 9ed1b74ed00a32e41906a8cbbdd50064, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
